Build a Snake game as a single self-contained HTML file
(HTML + CSS + JavaScript, no external dependencies or build step).

Requirements:
- A grid-based play area rendered on a <canvas>
- Arrow keys (and ideally WASD) control the snake's direction
- The snake grows by one segment each time it eats food; food respawns at a
  random empty cell
- Game over on collision with a wall or with the snake's own body
- Prevent instant 180-degree reversals (e.g. can't go straight from left to right)
- Display the current score and a game-over state with a way to restart
- Reasonable, constant game speed via a game loop

Don't use any frameworks or CDNs — plain vanilla JS. The whole thing should
run by opening the file in a browser.